The NES's main memory uses SRAM chips.  The only DRAM that I'm aware of is the OAM (SPR-RAM) and possibly the palette RAM, which are both integrated into the PPU.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Tue Dec 14, 2004 3:01 pm</p><hr />
